# Cursor IDE ‚Äî Cinematic Drama Agent Queue Orchestrator

This repo is a thin workspace for AI agents writing Cinematic Drama stories
for the Source2Draft ‚Üí Agent Queue API (`hlagency.net`, happykitemedia
WebApp). It is not the WebApp codebase, and it does not mirror the guide ‚Äî
only helper scripts and per-runtime entrypoints live here.

## Read first ‚Äî ALWAYS fetch the live guide, every session

This repo intentionally does not bundle the spec. Rules (genre handling,
concurrency caps, modes) change on the server first; a bundled copy here
would just go stale. So before anything else:

```bash
export AQ_BASE="https://hlagency.net/api/n8n/agent-queue"
export AQ_KEY="sk_ag_..."
export AQ_AGENT="<MACHINE_ID>-Cursor-orchestrator-1"
mkdir -p /tmp/agy_scratch
curl -s "$AQ_BASE/guide" -H "X-Automation-Key: $AQ_KEY" > /tmp/agy_scratch/GUIDE.md
curl -s "$AQ_BASE/qc"    -H "X-Automation-Key: $AQ_KEY" > /tmp/agy_scratch/cinematic_qc.py
```

Read `/tmp/agy_scratch/GUIDE.md` fully before claiming anything ‚Äî it is
authoritative: API, 7-stage pipeline, Revision/Social-Kit modes, quality
standards, Writer/Critic pattern, current concurrency cap. This file is only
a Cursor-specific operational summary; if it disagrees with `GUIDE.md`,
`GUIDE.md` wins.

## Runtime constraint

Cursor IDE has **no subagent spawn tool and no cron**. You play both roles
sequentially in the same session, strictly separated:

- **Writer role**: draft `task_<id>/{title,fb,comment,website,image_prompt}.txt`
  + `character_sheet.json` following `data.input.instructions` (7 stages, in
  order). Never grade your own draft.
- **Critic role**: judge the **files only** ‚Äî never your own drafting
  reasoning. Run `python3 /tmp/agy_scratch/cinematic_qc.py task_<id>/` as a hard
  gate first, then score the rubric (`TOTAL ‚â• 80`, `fb_hook ‚â• 17`,
  `comment_pull ‚â• 13` ‚Üí PASS; else fix the 2 lowest dimensions, max 3 soft
  rounds, best-of ‚â• 70 fallback).

One story at a time. Submit only after the Critic role returns PASS or
best-of.

## Hard rules

- **Do NOT edit any repository files** as your task output ‚Äî your only
  outputs are files under `/tmp/agy_scratch` and API calls. (Editing the
  scripts themselves, when the user explicitly asks you to update this
  repo, is fine ‚Äî this rule is about story-writing task output.)
- Never print task JSON or full story text into the terminal ‚Äî files +
  `python3` only (large source transcripts get truncated otherwise).
- Never commit or paste a real `AQ_KEY` / `sk_ag_...` into any file. Export it
  as a shell env var only.
- HARD 60-minute timeout from claim (up to 75 min with an active heartbeat ‚Äî
  a recent heartbeat buys up to 15 min of grace, but never rely on it;
  finish well under 60 min). `POST /<id>/heartbeat` regularly.

## Revision batches

For bulk `revision_note` queues (mechanical fixes, no fresh 7-step write),
check `GUIDE.md` for the revision-batch kickoff and use
`scripts/agent-worker/process_one_revision.sh` / `process_revision_batch.sh`.
